{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AEP6Kji4awJF9zuKzcU4yt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have gathered comprehensive information. Let me create a final summary of the codebase.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Understanding\n\n### 1. **package.json**\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `predev`: Runs migration before dev\n- `dev`: Runs ClickHouse server and Next.js concurrently with color-coded output\n- `build`: Next.js build\n- `start`: Next.js start\n- `migrate`: Runs migration script\n- `lint`: Biome check\n- `lint:fix`: Biome check with fixes\n- `test`: Vitest run (unit tests only)\n- `typecheck`: TypeScript validation\n\n**Dependencies:**\n- `@clickhouse/client`: ^1.18.2 - ClickHouse client\n- Material-UI: `@mui/material` (v9), `@emotion/react`, `@emotion/styled`, `@emotion/cache`\n- `@mui/material-nextjs`: Integration for Next.js\n- `next`: 16.2.3\n- `react`: 19.2.4, `react-dom`: 19.2.4\n\n**DevDependencies:**\n- `vitest`: ^4.1.4 - Unit test framework\n- `@playwright/test`: ^1.59.1 - E2E tests\n- `typescript`: ^5\n- `tailwindcss`: ^4 with `@tailwindcss/postcss`\n- `biome`: 2.2.0 - Linting/formatting\n- `tsx`: ^4.19.3 - TypeScript execution\n- `concurrently`: ^9.0.0 - Run multiple commands\n\n---\n\n### 2. **vitest.config.ts** - Full Content\n\n```typescript\nimport path from \"node:path\";\nimport { defaultExclude, defineConfig } from \"vitest/config\";\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  test: {\n    environment: \"node\",\n    exclude: [...defaultExclude, \"playwright_tests/**/*.spec.ts\"],\n  },\n  resolve: {\n    alias: { \"@\": path.resolve(__dirname, \"src\") },\n  },\n});\n```\n\n- Node environment (no browser simulation)\n- Excludes Playwright E2E tests\n- Path alias `@` points to `src/`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Test Files & Patterns**\n\n**Location Convention:** `src/{module}/__tests__/{filename}.test.ts` or `.integration.test.ts`\n\n**Naming:**\n- `*.test.ts` = Unit tests (with mocks, no DB)\n- `*.integration.test.ts` = Integration tests (real ClickHouse)\n\n**Test Structure Examples:**\n\n1. **Mocking Strategy** (from identity.test.ts):\n   - Use `vi.hoisted()` to hoist mock refs for `vi.mock()` factory\n   - Mock imports at module load time\n   - Helper functions like `mockQueryReturns()` for setup\n\n2. **Test Organization:**\n   - `describe()` blocks by feature/function\n   - `beforeEach()` / `afterEach()` for setup/teardown\n   - `afterEach()` always calls `vi.clearAllMocks()` and `vi.resetModules()`\n\n3. **Common Patterns:**\n   - Helper functions like `makeRequest()` to construct test inputs\n   - Sample data constants (e.g., `sampleEvent`)\n   - Test grouping by success/error scenarios\n\n---\n\n### 4. **src/app/explore/page.tsx** - Current State\n\nSimple placeholder using MUI Typography:\n```typescript\nexport default function ExplorePage(): React.JSX.Element {\n  return (\n    <Typography variant=\"h4\" component=\"h1\">\n      Explore\n    </Typography>\n  );\n}\n```\n\nOther placeholder pages follow same pattern (Generate, Test, Trends, Users, Funnels).\n\n---\n\n### 5. **src/lib/clickhouse.ts** - Client Singleton\n\nMinimal singleton export:\n```typescript\nexport const clickhouse = createClient({\n  url: process.env.CLICKHOUSE_URL ?? \"http://localhost:8123\",\n  database: process.env.CLICKHOUSE_DB ?? \"minipanel\",\n  password: process.env.CLICKHOUSE_PASSWORD ?? \"password\",\n});\n```\n\nEnv defaults ensure it works in dev without .env setup.\n\n---\n\n### 6. **src/lib/identity.ts** - EventRow Type & Functions\n\n**Key Exports:**\n\n1. **Types:**\n   - `EventInput`: Input for event ingestion (event_name required, device_id OR user_id required, optional timestamp/properties)\n   - `EventRow`: Persisted event with all fields (device_id/user_id/properties nullable, includes ingested_at timestamp and resolved_id)\n   - `QueryEventsOptions`: Filtering options (event_name, resolved_id, before cursor, limit)\n\n2. **Functions:**\n\n   **`validateEvent(input: unknown): asserts input is EventInput`**\n   - Type guard that throws on invalid input\n   - Requires non-empty event_name and at least one of device_id/user_id\n\n   **`insertEvent(input, client?): Promise<EventRow>`**\n   - Validates event\n   - Auto-generates event_id (UUID), ingested_at (current time)\n   - Uses provided timestamp or current time\n   - Serializes properties to JSON string\n   - If both device_id AND user_id provided, calls `resolveIdentityMapping()`\n   - Returns EventRow with resolved_id = user_id ?? device_id ?? \"\"\n   - Throws IdentityConflictError (status 409) on identity conflict\n\n   **`resolveIdentityMapping(device_id, user_id, client?): Promise<void>`**\n   - Queries identity_mappings FINAL for existing device → user mapping\n   - If found with same user_id: no-op (idempotent)\n   - If found with different user_id: throws IdentityConflictError (409)\n   - If not found: inserts new mapping\n   - Idempotent by design\n\n   **`queryEventsWithResolvedId(options?, client?): Promise<EventRow[]>`**\n   - Returns events with resolved_id = coalesce(e.user_id, m.user_id, e.device_id)\n   - Supports optional filters: event_name, resolved_id, before (cursor), limit (max 200, default 50)\n   - Ordered by timestamp DESC, event_id DESC\n   - LEFT JOINs identity_mappings FINAL for user mappings\n\n   **`getEventsByResolvedId(resolved_id, client?): Promise<EventRow[]>`**\n   - Convenience wrapper around queryEventsWithResolvedId\n   - Returns up to 200 events for a given resolved identity\n\n3. **Error:**\n   - `IdentityConflictError` extends Error with `status = 409`\n   - Custom constructor maintains prototype chain\n\n---\n\n### 7. **src/app/api/events/list/route.ts** - Events List API\n\n**GET /api/events/list**\n\nQuery params (optional):\n- `event_name`: Filter by event name\n- `resolved_id`: Filter by resolved identity\n- `before`: Cursor (timestamp) for pagination\n- `limit`: Results per page (default 50, max 200, must be positive)\n\nResponse:\n```json\n{\n  \"events\": [EventRow[], ...],\n  \"next_cursor\": \"ISO-timestamp\" | null\n}\n```\n\nnext_cursor is set to last event's timestamp only if results.length === limit (indicates more pages exist).\n\nError handling:\n- 400 if limit is invalid (non-numeric, zero, negative)\n\n---\n\n### 8. **src/app/api/schema/route.ts** - Schema API\n\n**GET /api/schema**\n\nReturns:\n```json\n{\n  \"event_names\": [\"string\", ...],\n  \"properties\": {\n    \"event_name\": {\n      \"property_key\": \"numeric\" | \"string\",\n      ...\n    },\n    ...\n  }\n}\n```\n\nImplementation:\n- Samples last 10,000 events\n- Uses JSONExtractKeys to enumerate property keys\n- Detects numeric types: JSONExtractFloat returns non-null, non-zero value\n- Groups by event_name and property_key\n- 60-second in-memory cache (uses schema-cache.ts)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **src/lib/schema-cache.ts** - Schema Cache\n\n**Exports:**\n\n1. **`getCachedSchema(): SchemaResponse | null`**\n   - Returns cached schema if exists and within TTL (60s)\n   - Returns null if expired or never set\n\n2. **`setCachedSchema(value: SchemaResponse): void`**\n   - Stores schema with current timestamp\n\n3. **`invalidateSchemaCache(): void`**\n   - Clears cache entry (used in tests and on data changes)\n\nModule state: Single `let entry: CacheEntry | null`\n\nTTL: 60,000ms (60 seconds)\n\n---\n\n### 10. **src/app/layout.tsx** - Layout\n\nRoot layout with:\n- AppRouterCacheProvider for MUI + Next.js\n- Geist font families for sans and mono\n- Metadata: title \"MiniPanel\", description \"Self-hosted product analytics\"\n- Flex layout: Sidebar on left (fixed width 240px), main content area flex-1\n- Global CSS import\n- Tailwind classes for responsive layout (h-full, min-h-full, min-h-screen)\n\n---\n\n### 11. **src/components/Sidebar.tsx** - Navigation Sidebar\n\nClient component (\"use client\" directive).\n\nFeatures:\n- MUI Drawer (permanent variant, width 240px)\n- Navigation items defined as constant array:\n  - Explore (`/explore`)\n  - Trends (`/trends`)\n  - Funnels (`/funnels`)\n  - Users (`/users`)\n  - Test (`/test`)\n  - Generate (`/generate`)\n- Uses `usePathname()` to highlight current route\n- Next.js Link integration for client-side navigation\n- MUI Typography header \"MiniPanel\"\n\n---\n\n### 12. **Component Files in src/components/**\n\nCurrently only:\n- `Sidebar.tsx`\n\nOther pages (Explore, Trends, Funnels, Users, Test, Generate) are placeholder pages with basic Typography heading. No reusable components exist yet beyond Sidebar.\n\n---\n\n### **Key Architectural Patterns**\n\n1. **Database Layer:**\n   - Singleton ClickHouse client (src/lib/clickhouse.ts)\n   - Type-safe queries with query_params\n   - JSONEachRow format for request/response\n\n2. **Testing:**\n   - Unit tests with mocked dependencies (vi.mock)\n   - Integration tests with real ClickHouse\n   - __tests__ folder colocated with module\n   - beforeEach/afterEach for isolation\n   - vi.hoisted() for mock factory refs\n\n3. **API Routes:**\n   - req/res patterns with Response.json()\n   - Query param parsing from URL.searchParams\n   - Error responses with status codes (400, 409, 500)\n   - Delegated business logic to lib/\n\n4. **UI:**\n   - MUI for components\n   - Tailwind for layout/utilities\n   - Server components by default\n   - Client-side navigation via Next.js Link\n\n5. **Types:**\n   - Explicit interface exports (EventInput, EventRow, SchemaResponse)\n   - TypeScript strict mode enabled\n   - Type guards with asserts keyword\n\n---\n\n**Absolute File Paths for Reference:**\n\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/package.json`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/vitest.config.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/clickhouse.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/identity.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/lib/schema-cache.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/events/list/route.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/api/schema/route.ts`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/layout.tsx`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/components/Sidebar.tsx`\n- `/Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2/src/app/explore/page.tsx` (placeholder)"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b55bde5a-8012-4aca-b30e-7084df65edbe","uuid":"301db3f5-6002-4401-996c-0597b1c80b90","timestamp":"2026-04-15T16:25:58.678Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase at /Users/riccardocaranfil/bitrefill/minipanel-blank-night-2 and give me a thorough understanding of:\n\n1. The package.json (scripts, dependencies, devDependencies)\n2. vitest.config.ts or vitest.config.js - full content\n3. The existing test files (find examples of test files to understand naming conventions and patterns)\n4. src/app/explore/page.tsx - current placeholder content\n5. src/lib/clickhouse.ts - client singleton\n6. src/lib/identity.ts - EventRow type and queryEventsWithResolvedId function\n7. src/app/api/events/list/route.ts - the events list API\n8. src/app/api/schema/route.ts - the schema API\n9. src/lib/schema-cache.ts - schema cache\n10. src/app/layout.tsx - layout\n11. src/components/Sidebar.tsx\n12. Any existing component files in src/components/\n\nBe thorough - I need to understand existing patterns before implementing new code.","agentId":"a315f304667e84e47","agentType":"Explore","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! I have gathered comprehensive information. Let me create a final summary of the codebase.\n\n## Comprehensive Codebase Understanding\n\n### 1. **package.json**\n\n**Scripts:**\n- `predev`: Runs migration before dev\n- `dev`: Runs ClickHouse server and Next.js concurrently with color-coded output\n- `build`: Next.js build\n- `