{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QozzuDNvnbhxXvF5vkK9EY","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The tests are failing because rendering accumulates across tests - previous renders are not cleaned up between tests. The `render()` from `@testing-library/react` v14+ has automatic cleanup. But the issue here is that all renders from previous tests are accumulating in the body.\n\nActually, looking at the error: \"Found multiple elements with the role 'link'\" - this suggests that the `render()` calls from multiple tests are accumulating without cleanup.\n\n`@testing-library/react` v16 has automatic cleanup via `afterEach`. But this cleanup needs to be registered. \n\nThe auto-cleanup should be triggered automatically in vitest since `@testing-library/react` detects the testing framework's `afterEach` hook, but it's possible I need to explicitly import and call `cleanup` to ensure it's working properly. The error showing multiple renders of the same element suggests the auto-cleanup isn't firing between tests. I'm realizing the auto-cleanup might not be triggering properly with the jsdom environment directive, so I need to explicitly import and call `cleanup()` from `@testing-library/react` in the `afterEach` hook of both test files to ensure each test starts with a clean DOM.\n\nThe failures in `IdentityChip.test.tsx` and `JsonChip.test.tsx` are all stemming from the same issue—multiple elements being found because previous test renders aren't being cleared between tests. The `useEventExplorer.test.ts` tests passed, which suggests the hook tests don't have this DOM pollution problem.\n\nLooking more carefully at the error messages, I see that both the empty string and empty object tests are leaving their rendered chips in the DOM. The real issue is that `@testing-library/react` v16 only auto-cleans up if `afterEach` is globally available, but vitest doesn't inject globals by default—it requires `globals: true` in the config, which isn't set here. So cleanup isn't happening automatically, and I need to manually add it to the test files.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4597,"cache_read_input_tokens":80825,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":4597},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b55bde5a-8012-4aca-b30e-7084df65edbe","uuid":"e46a5870-cacd-455f-bb50-0549efc9518c"}
